The bone house is still fascinating after 100 years. take a look at Gaudi's interiors.
The roof looks like the back of a prehistoric savarian, the staircase to a dinosaur's spine and the balconies to open fish mouths.
This is the house Casa Battlo in Barcelona by architect Antoni Gaudi.
Due to its organic shapes, the house received from the locals the surname of House in bones.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stones, fragments of squares and mosaic, facade reminding of scales and everywhere present curves, this is all that is epic for Antoni Gaudi's New Art.
The front facade of the house plays its dream lines, its pleasant colors and texture that remind nature and animals.
During a more detailed observation we see the geometry, the rhythm and order thought with accuracy.
In the night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lighted in such a way that the brightness of the colors is strengthened.
The rolling and turning of the shapes also appears in the interior with the same measurement.
The wood copies into waves the windows frame, the balustrades, the decorative elements of the doors, the eyelid and the lamels.
The Battlo house which stands in the Eixample neighborhood in the shopping street Passeig de Gracia at number. 43, was born from the construction of a house of 1877 by the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction was done for two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a rich entrepreneur, first insisted on the demolition of the old building and the construction of another completely new but quickly accepted Gaudi’s idea of an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as a multi-housing house was not thought by Gaudi alone.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It is just on his project that the decorations for a representative apartment of the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade were born.
For the facade also worked other artists and creators.
The joint work for the plans of the Casa Battlo house began with a successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of Gaudi's house Casa Mila and the Guell Park in which there are other works of Gaudi.
The locals called the house hot just after its completion because of its organic shapes "the house in bones".
Others, given the specific mechanism of opening windows, called it "the house that dances".
It is said that at the top of the building there is a sword similar to that of St. George the patron of Catalonia.
Other sculpture elements of the construction contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudi thought for the house a unique system in its central heating time,with typical airing events and chemins.
Their inclination of 45 degrees seems strange.
During the creation Gaudi absolutely did not comply with the construction guidelines of that time and did not let himself be hindered by them.
At the beginning of the construction it was obtained from the city the permission to build, knowing, of course, that the data drawn on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the completion the municipal council was horrifying and requested changes.
For example, the members of the municipal council did not like that the pillars of the construction stumbled on the public trottoir.
There was never a change, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the call of the city Josep Battlo asked (and obtained satisfaction) the permission to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and on the third a room and a private part of the apartment.
The floor was rented to a jewelry store.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase through which you can access to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and right lines were cancelled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and replaced by curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of space connection.
The common part can be fully connected by opening the doors of the salons and the high company can communicate comfortably or limit private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with Gaudi's reconstruction, in addition to new facades, received a non-traditional roof and two more floors.
The game of Gaudi with the light is also impressive, blue and white glass plates with which the interior courtyard is decorated and with the bricks of light.
The two-colored game gives the maximum light in every floor of the house.
It was simply enough to bet on the principle that white reflects more than dark which, on the contrary, absorbs the sun’s rays.
The Casa Battlo house which was registered in 2005 in the UNESCO World Heritage Fund may be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the famous creator's birth.
They continued the visits because they found that it was a profitable business and they expanded the field of visits to common spaces and ground floor including roof terraces.
The entrance ticket to the monument is really not expensive and costs 16.50 euros; students, retirees, groups and tourist cards holders have a 20% discount.
The amount is still above the entrance price in the other Gaudi buildings in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic towers, you need to quickly find a companion among the inhabitants of the building and fully visit the house.
