The generals believe that this new automatic gun will have an influence on the conflict there with the Taliban and will “change the game” to their benefit.
The new weapon is like a super-precision canon.
Its projectiles are directed by laser with a precision of a few meters.
The special ammunition of 25 mm calibre developed for this gun and containing a highly broken explosive, actually works like small grenades.
The ammunition can be programmed in such a way that it will explode at the contact of the target but also at any point of their ballistic trajectory.
Therefore, it can be used against an enemy that is hidden behind an obstacle, a wall or a gap.
It is not also protected from the top and when a deadly rain falls on it of steel shells, it can put it out of fight as well.
According to Richard Audette who took part in the development of the XM-25, the new gun is the first infantry weapon that uses the “intelligent” technology.
“The soldier uses it essentially in such a way that he finds the target, sends him a laser radius that determines the distance, thus obtains a precise target point, according to which he corrects his target site and pushes on the relaxation.
“Let’s say you’ve targeted 543 meters.”
“When you press the relaxation, the weapon is charged and shot at a distance of 543 meters more or less 1, 2, 3 meters,” Audette said.
