“We want to know what are, for example, the incidences of genetically modified corn cause to the field,” says Mr. Then.
The current practice consists in testing only the isolated proteins and not the whole genetically modified plant, which does not allow to obtain reliable results.
“If we don’t look for the risks, how can we then discover them?” asked Mr. Then in an accusing tone.
This is also the point of view of Mrs. Angelika Hilbeck.
