EU changes rules for visa
People must go to the Visa Applicants Service Centers before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost the waiting time will be reduced.
From 10 January 2011 the visa processing procedure at the U.S. Embassy and Consulates will be changed.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to present themselves to the Visa Applicants Service Centers (ASC) before their interview in the Consular Section.
ASC staff will take the applicant’s biometric information, which will be reviewed by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will present certain advantages for aspirants, among which the following are mentioned:
The total cost of processing the visa will be lower, it will no longer be necessary to make a payment to get a date, another payment for the visa processing and another for the postal service to deliver the document.
The aspirant will make a single payment that will cover the three services.
The current fee will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in the case of visa with request (this includes visas for temporary workers) and $390 for traders and investors' visas.
People who wish to renew their visa will not have to attend an interview with the Consular Representative, they will only present themselves at the nearest ASC where they will present the documents and their footprints will be taken.
Due to the fact that biometric information will be taken in the ASC, applicants who want a second date to be interviewed in the Consular Section will stay there less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants at the Consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer pay the $26 extra service fee.
For more information about the new visa application procedure, visit the following page http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
